	<!-- Professional Bio Section -->
	<section id="bio" class="section">
		<h2>About Me</h2>
		
		<div class="bio-grid">
			<div class="bio-text">
				<p class="lead">
					I'm a Computer Science graduate passionate about creating technology that enhances 
					human potential rather than constraining it. My journey from struggling with poorly 
					designed educational technology to leading international EdTech development has 
					shaped my deep commitment to human-centered design principles.
				</p>
				
				<p>
					Growing up in Louisiana's under-resourced education system and experiencing firsthand 
					how broken technology like Edgenuity can undermine learning, I've developed a keen 
					interest in the psychology behind human-technology interactions. This background 
					drives my work to create AI systems that adapt to human cognitive diversity rather 
					than forcing humans to adapt to technological limitations.
				</p>
				
				<p>
					My experience spans from developing AI-powered accessibility tools to architecting 
					collaborative learning platforms that prioritize human agency. I'm particularly 
					drawn to research that explores how humans adapt to, resist, and ultimately improve 
					AI systems—insights that could contribute valuable real-world perspective to 
					understanding the psychology of human-AI relationships.
				</p>
			</div>
			
